trans-unit.source:
A seed phrase (sometimes called a Mnemonic), is a collection of random words used to create a private key, that will in turn create a wallet.
This phrase or collection of words acts as a recovery mechanism for you to retrieve your wallet on another app, phone, computer, web app etc. The same words will always produce the same wallet.
It is critically important to write these words down, in order, and keep a paper backup. It is NOT possible to recover them any other way.
If you delete your app, reset you phone, or a critical secutiry update is needed that deletes the data from the app ... you will have no other way to access your funds without that phrase

trans-unit.source:
CustomAuth is the name of a service provided by the Torus Network.
Originally created for the Ethereum network, and now updated to work with Tezos, Torus allows you to create a wallet by logging into a third party provider. Such as "Sign in with Apple", Twitter, Google, Facebook, Reddit etc.
Instead of having to remember extra details and passwords for your wallet, you can just login with the provider of your choice.
Note: While doing this makes using the blockchain easier, be aware of the fact that you loose anonimity this way. Anyone could type in your Twitter/Facebook username, google email etc, and get your wallet address.

trans-unit.source:
Think of a Wallet as your bank account, on the blockchain. Its where you store all your tokens, NFT's, earn interest etc.
Walletss have an address That comes with a prefix of "TZ1", "TZ2" or "TZ3". Sometimes referred to as you "TZ address".
It is safe to give this address to other people, as they can't do anything with this address, other than make transfer to you, or view its details on a blockchian explorer
